1. CatBoost photon-identification models  (src/photonid/models/)
---------------------------------------------------------------

Files:
    RGA_inbending_pass1.hpp
    RGA_inbending_pass2.hpp
    RGA_outbending_pass1.hpp
    RGA_outbending_pass2.hpp
    RGC_Summer2022_pass1.hpp

These are generated CatBoost gradient-boosted-tree models used to identify
photons in the CLAS12 electromagnetic calorimeter. They are trained CLAS12
products, distributed as part of:

    Iguana -- Implementation Guardian of Analysis Algorithms
    https://github.com/JeffersonLab/iguana
    Jefferson Lab, Hall B / CLAS12 Collaboration
    Licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License v3.0

specifically as
    src/iguana/algorithms/clas12/PhotonGBTFilter/models/*.cpp

The copies in this repository are byte-for-byte identical in payload to
Iguana's: 203,339 numeric tokens per model, verified token-by-token. They
reached this repository via an intermediate copy, but Iguana is their origin
and the licence above is the one that governs them.

They are unmodified. Only the file extension differs (.cpp -> .hpp), because
here they are included rather than compiled as separate translation units.

Because these files are incorporated into this work, this repository is
distributed under the LGPL v3.0 as well -- see COPYING.LESSER (the LGPL v3
supplement) and COPYING (the GPL v3 text it builds on). LGPL v3 consists of
both.


